Best Practices for Professional Prompting
1. Ask Questions First
Always encourage the AI to request missing information before generating the final output.
Example:
“Before answering, ask me any important questions needed for accuracy.”
2. Define the Role Clearly
Giving the AI a role improves relevance and professionalism.
Example:
“You are an experienced corporate lawyer.”
3. Specify Tone and Audience
Outputs become more accurate when the intended audience is defined.
4. Use Structured Formatting
Structured prompts produce cleaner, more organized responses.
5. Include Constraints
Examples:
Word limits
Formality level
Output format
Timeline requirements
